audio tape or mp3 file, and hence could not
be verified.

46:05.390 --> 46:10.150
) call as Gudi Padwa, Padwa means first day
of the moon is Padwa, and Gudi means “this”.

46:10.150 --> 46:20.839
So they put it up and that is how they say
that today is the New Year day for the Shalivahanas.

46:20.839 --> 46:34.239
Shawl is the covering of your Mother which
gives it warmth and also it covers Her modesty.

46:34.239 --> 46:41.450
Shawl is a sign of regality and modesty and
chastity.

46:41.450 --> 46:42.979
So you stand for that of your Mother.

46:42.979 --> 46:53.400
You protect it like Ganesha does.

46:53.400 --> 47:00.130
Only on one point He gets angry, if anybody
says or does anything against the Mother,

47:00.130 --> 47:03.529
then He comes down.

47:03.529 --> 47:09.449
That’s why Christ has said: “Anything
against Me I’ll tolerate, but anything against

47:09.449 --> 47:14.299
the Holy Ghost, will not be forgiven.

47:14.299 --> 47:22.180
” That’s the Son talking about the Mother,
that’s what happens.

47:22.180 --> 47:25.589
So today is the second day.

47:25.589 --> 47:38.269
Second day is the Bija – is the they call
it the Bhav-bija is the day when the brother

47:38.269 --> 47:49.299
and the sister, who are the seeds of one tree
have that pure exchange of affection.

47:49.299 --> 47:55.209
The sister does the aarti of the brother,
gives him a tika and then brother gives her

47:55.209 --> 47:59.150
something as a token of his love, as a present.

47:59.150 --> 48:04.410
In Bombay we started that and they have made
sisters and brothers.

48:04.410 --> 48:08.299
I wish you also could find out somebody as
a nice brother.

48:08.299 --> 48:19.199
But I found that these relationships have
been so beautifully managed in India that

48:19.199 --> 48:27.999
if they could be managed here, it will be
a great day of really ecstasy for Me, because

48:27.999 --> 48:34.170
that means you have overcome this devil of
immorality.

48:34.170 --> 48:42.499
The purity, removing the lust and greed from
your mind completely and bestowing that affection

48:42.499 --> 48:47.170
for someone who is your sister.

48:47.170 --> 48:51.910
Very common in India, everybody has a sister
there; all the Sahaja Yogis have a sister

48:51.910 --> 48:55.509
and they look after their sister that way.

48:55.509 --> 49:02.969
Is a very sweet feeling and a sister is treated
– like Raulbai is a sister of Dumas you

49:02.969 --> 49:10.430
can imagine, and her sister is treated with
the same grace as the own sister is to be

49:10.430 --> 49:13.880
treated with all the relationships and everything.

49:13.880 --> 49:17.189
So this is the fifth day is Dwija.

49:17.189 --> 49:22.410
So from thirteenth to the fifth day they celebrate
Diwali.

49:22.410 --> 49:25.779
For us Diwali has a very great significance.

49:25.779 --> 49:35.400
That is, from one light many lights are awakened
and they are put in a line, so they are called

49:35.400 --> 49:39.309
as Diwali – means ‘the lights put in a
line’.

49:39.309 --> 49:47.650
So when you hold My Hands together all of
us – through that the energy passes and

49:47.650 --> 50:02.019
the enlightened rasa is established, and the
whole world has to become that beautiful reign

50:02.019 --> 50:18.059
of your Mother where nothing but the bliss
of your Father and His enjoyment when He sees

50:18.059 --> 50:24.569
His Own Creation dancing in that Ocean of
Bliss.

50:24.569 --> 50:26.720
May God bless you.
